RESOURCES NAMES AND THEIR ARGUMENTS FOR AWS IN TERRAFORM HCL LANGUAGE
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

🖥️ 1️⃣ aws_instance (EC2)

Used for: Creating virtual servers
Important arguments:

ami → OS image ID

instance_type → Type of instance (e.g., t2.micro)

key_name → SSH key pair name

security_groups → Attach security groups

tags → Name or labels

☁️ 2️⃣ aws_s3_bucket

Used for: Creating S3 storage buckets
Important arguments:

bucket → Bucket name

acl → Access type (e.g., private, public-read)

versioning → Enable version control

tags → Bucket labels

🌐 3️⃣ aws_vpc

Used for: Creating a virtual private cloud
Important arguments:

cidr_block → IP range for the VPC

enable_dns_support → DNS enable/disable

tags → Name or labels

🕸️ 4️⃣ aws_subnet

Used for: Creating a subnet inside a VPC
Important arguments:

vpc_id → Associated VPC

cidr_block → Subnet IP range

availability_zone → Region zone

tags → Labels

🔐 5️⃣ aws_security_group   //used in terraform environment based project in uat environment

Used for: Managing firewall rules
Important arguments:

vpc_id → Associated VPC

ingress → Inbound rules

egress → Outbound rules

tags → Name or labels

🌍 6️⃣ aws_internet_gateway

Used for: Giving VPC access to the internet
Important arguments:

vpc_id → VPC to attach

tags → Labels

📋 7️⃣ aws_route_table

Used for: Defining routes in a VPC
Important arguments:

vpc_id → Associated VPC

route → Route configuration

tags → Labels

🔑 8️⃣ aws_key_pair

Used for: Creating SSH key for EC2 access
Important arguments:

key_name → Name of key

public_key → Public key value

